Author: BOLLINGER
Vol / Page: 79
Edition:
Quote: There is probably no need to ask why, when the bare majority was finally adopted in 1919, a third issue (State Control) was added to the ballot paper, with the permanent effect.. of splitting the anti-trade vote. <i> Ibid. </i>  80 It is certainly true that from 1919 to 1925 the State Control vote was bigger than the difference between the Continuance and Prohibition votes. <i> Ibid</i> 165 The trade's chief complaint against the Bill was that it would be a high road to a "State Control of the trade."
