Date: 19/8/1904
Source: Nelson Evening Mail
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: As a member of that renowned Wai-iti Literary Society, which is responsible for the controversy now being carried on in your columns on that interesting and burning question, "State Control of the Liquor Traffic versus Prohibition," I would sir, in justice to Mr Wright and the other gentlemen who journeyed to Wai-iti to take part in the debate under discussion, to point out that it was quite understood by all concerned that the debate should be of a friendly character, and that no feeling should be shown on either side.
